<!-- Security & Trust Section -->
<section id="security" class="ai-services-module section">
	<div class="container">
		<h2 class="section-title">Security & Trust</h2>
		<p class="section-intro">Your automations run on proven, secure platforms; including OpenAI's Agent Builder,
		Zapier, Make, n8n, and Workato; trusted by thousands of businesses worldwide.</p>
		<div class="vertical-list">
			<div class="service-card">
				<h3 class="card-title">Data Ownership</h3>
				<p class="card-description">
					You always own your data and workflows. Eleoro doesn't store or resell your information; all data stays
					within your connected platforms such as Salesforce, HubSpot, or Shopify.
				</p>
				<hr>
				<h3 class="card-title">Encryption</h3>
				<p class="card-description">
					All connections use TLS 1.2+ encryption in transit and AES-256 encryption at rest. For example, Zapier
					encrypts authentication tokens and Workato encrypts customer payloads before storage.
				</p>
				<hr>
				<h3 class="card-title">Compliance</h3>
				<p class="card-description">
					Platforms like OpenAI's Agent Builder, Zapier, Make, n8n, and Workato maintain SOC 2 Type II, GDPR, and CCPA
					compliance. HIPAA-eligible plans are available when required.
				</p>
				<hr>
				<h3 class="card-title">Access Control</h3>
				<p class="card-description">
					Role-based permissions ensure that only authorised team members can modify workflows or credentials.
					Example: n8n supports per-user roles and Workato provides granular workspace access.
				</p>
				<hr>
				<h3 class="card-title">Audits</h3>
				<p class="card-description">
					Each connected platform undergoes regular third-party security assessments and updates. You can view
					individual audit reports directly from each provider's Trust or Security portal.
				</p>
				<hr>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
